<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[286,1195,2553,2828]" pageId="19" pageNumber="272" type="mainText">
Shrub. Leaves succulent, scale-like. Flowers in groups of 3 in the axils of short, opposite, free bracts; perianth 3-lobed, fleshy, membranous in fruit; lobes connate to below the apex; stamen 1; stigmas 2. Embryo semi-annular; radicle inferior. One sp., 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Halostachys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="belangerianum">H. belangerianum (Moq.) Botsch.</taxonomicName>
, SW and C Asia.
</paragraph>
